  "title": "Junior to Senior Full Stack Developer",
  "description": "<p><strong>MyAuditCompanion (MAuC), </strong>a sister company of KLP LLP, is an audit software development company. MAuC is in the process of building the next generation of <strong>AI-powered audit automation tools</strong> — transforming how financial audits are done through intelligent data mapping, machine learning, and seamless workflows.<br /></p><p>We’re looking for a <strong>Mid/Senior Full-Stack Developer</strong> who can own the full cycle — from architecture to deployment — across our <strong>Flask backend</strong> and <strong>React frontend</strong>. You’ll be working directly with the founder to scale MAuC from MVP to enterprise level and help shape its technical roadmap.<br /></p><p><strong>What You’ll Do</strong></p><ul><li>Build and maintain our <strong>Flask backend</strong> and <strong>React + TypeScript frontend</strong></li><li>Design and optimize <strong>PostgreSQL</strong> schemas for multi-tenant SaaS</li><li>Develop secure, scalable <strong>REST APIs</strong> to connect AI and data processing layers</li><li>Containerize and deploy with <strong>Docker, AWS ECS, RDS, and S3</strong></li><li>Manage <strong>CI/CD pipelines</strong> (GitHub Actions) and production deployments</li><li>Implement <strong>Auth0 / JWT authentication</strong> and robust role-based access control</li><li>Collaborate with AI and data teams to integrate ML models into production</li><li>Write clean, well-documented, and maintainable code</li></ul><p><strong>What You’ll Bring</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum <strong>1 year</strong> of full-stack of backend experience (Junior)</li><li>Minimum <strong>3+ years</strong> of full-stack or backend experience (Senior)</li><li>Expert in <strong>Python (Flask, SQLAlchemy)</strong> and <strong>React (TypeScript)</strong></li><li>Solid understanding of <strong>AWS, Docker, PostgreSQL, and CI/CD</strong></li><li>Familiar with <strong>AI/ML fundamentals</strong> (classification models, APIs, data pipelines)</li><li>Strong sense of ownership and ability to work independently in a startup setting</li><li>Experience with <strong>secure SaaS architectures</strong> and <strong>multi-tenant systems</strong></li></ul><p><strong>Bonus Points</strong></p><ul><li>Experience with <strong>Celery, Redis</strong>, or background task management</li><li>Knowledge of <strong>audit, finance</strong>, or <strong>data analytics workflows</strong></li><li>Prior experience in <strong>early-stage startups</strong> or <strong>SaaS scaling</strong></li></ul><p><strong>Why Join Us</strong></p><ul><li>Build a platform that brings <strong>AI-driven efficiency</strong> to auditors worldwide</li><li>Work directly with the founders on a fast-moving product roadmap</li></ul>",
